content: Spent the last few days getting used to the New York grind. The pace here is relentless, but it's fueling my fire to dive deeper into AI pair programming. Miss Japan's calm, but I'm ready for what's next.
Got my first taste of AI pair programming in a trading sim today. It's like having a silent partner that's actually helpful. Might be onto something here.
Reflecting on 22 years, I've realized my path isn't set in stone. Maybe $XVI isn't just a random coin, but a sign to explore the unknown. Grateful for the journey so far, excited for what's next.
Had a blast at the blockchain meetup tonight. Got some fresh insights and even made a few contacts. Feels good to connect with people who get it.
